\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid14504576 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Now, you said you were born in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 1896.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 And whereabouts were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 In Solin (?) Street, Stoke.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 What sort of a house was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Oh it was a small terraced house, smaller even than this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How many rooms were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
 up and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  down. With an outside lavatory and coalhouse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Oh I see. Had you a garden at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 No. No, garden. There was no garden. Just a yard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 What were your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  downstairs rooms then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Oh a room like this which we called the kitchen and the one which we called the back kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 And what did you have in the back kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Oh there was a sink, and the washing was done in the back kitchen, and the cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Had you a stove or a range or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 At that time no. Cooking was done on a hanging plate. I don't know it you understand that one? Well a hanging plat
e is, you have got to imagine it's a type of range, but it wasn't a big range hotting hot water, it had just got one oven and when you cooked anything, if you didn't use the other, say for breakfast bacon and things like that, it had 2 hooks that hung on 
t
he bars, on the fire, and a flat plate, this was made of steel, a steel plate, that you could move about either nearer to the fire, you pushed it right up to the bars if you wanted, and bacon and things like that was cooked on that you see. Or if you want
ed toasted cheese or anything like that welsh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
arebit, you used this, otherwise you used over the top of the fire, which we called broiling, and you had the meat on a toasting fork arrangement and as it began to cook, you used to put the bread underneath it
 and let the fat drip onto it you see, otherwise it dropped into the fire and caused a smoke. And er -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Would your mother bake her bread or would you buy bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 We bought bread. There was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 7}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  children, I'm next to the youngest. My father was a sto
ne mason. And me mother of course was occupied in the house because my father was a drunkard and he didn't bring much money in at that time, by present standards he would probably be an alcoholic. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 Although he came from a better family than what me mother '
cos his father was a master crate maker and but he was a stone mason, all his brothers were in the business with his father but he wouldn't have it and he was a stone mason and although I say it myself he was a good stone mason, in fact he was a foreman s
tone mason, and he made grave stones and apart from that he was foreman for the biggest building contractor in the potteries at that time which was Thomas \{BLANK\}. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
And he used to be in charge of houses that were stone built, you know, and he was in charge of all the stonework. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 
And one of the places which he built is Stardon Hall, which is the nurses' home of the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Stardon{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Orthopaedic
{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Hospital{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
Do you know it? Well I was in there because I was, on the knee cap, I smashed a knee cap, I was operated on in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 
And he was doing that sort of work and while he was doing that sort of work that really was the cause of his death because he used to walk to work through {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Trentham
{\*\xmlclose} }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, do you know {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Trentham
{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}? And he used to get on to the Beech (?) Road which as you know, if you know Stardon you go right up the Beech Road, I don't know if you can get up now because \{BLANK
\} but he walked into one of the pools in Trentham Park and he caught pneumonia and he died when he was 49. i.e born - 1857. he was 40 when he was born.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 I was 10.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How did your mother manage then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
Oh she did charring. She took washing. She worked right until the time of her death. At 57. And she was office cleaning, she used to take washing in and my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  el
dest sisters used to go and help her in the morning. She cleaned the National Provincial Bank in Stoke and at night-time they used to go to a solicitors office, Frank Collis (?), near the King's Hall and in between they went to work, they used to have to 
turn out early in the morning, come home have their breakfast, get washed and changed and go to work and at night-time they came home and had tea and were out again until }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  o'clock at night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 What sort of jobs were they doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 One sister was in t
he warehouse of Gasses the china, well porcelain manufacturer, he used to make, I don't know if you know them, they were fancy ornaments with badges on them. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
Well we used to have a house full at one time. That was me next to eldest sister. And me eldest sister was a decorator on Spode, Copeland. And they carried on like that right until they both got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How about your brothers, what did they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 I had one who worked as a crate maker in his grandfather's place you see, which was at Longton, 
and then work got slack and he went to work at Kirst Hewitt's (?) I don't know if you have heard of that? They used to build engines for the Indian State Railways and things like that. And then they went smash and he finished up working at Midgley's until
 he died, well until he retired. He is dead now. And the next brother was an engine driver, he died when he was 53. Then my next brother older than me he was a bit of a - couldn't settle anywhere, he has been all round the world. 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}India{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Persia{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Palestine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 {\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, t
he Army, all the lot. And I have a young sister who is still living, she didn't do much work, she worked as an apprentice milliner, a good shop in Piccadilly there which has gone now. It is Pepper (?)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 s motor showroom now. And then she worked in P.M.T. off
ices and then they wanted her to stop late at night, in the meantime my mother had died, and that left only her and me at home. Because this brother next to me was away in Persia I think at the time, but anyway she came home one night from the office and 
she said her boss had asked her to stop until }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  o'clock at night, well she was only about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
teen and she said there was no overtime pay for it and so I said to her "Well look, tell him you are finished, you can come and keep house for me" at that time I was working in the pit. I went in the pit just before the 1918 War started.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 So when your father died your mother had several other wages coming into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes. My eldest brother got married shortly after my father died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 I see. But she did have some money, it wasn't entirely what she earned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Oh no, it wasn't all that she had. But we were always very poor. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 
Yes, very, very poor. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 For instance we had a joint at the weekend, and then on the Monday it was cold meat, which was Sunday's joint
 of course, and then on Tuesday what was left of the joint would be stewed up and then towards the weekend we might have boiled rice. For dinner. It wasn't boiled in milk, it was boiled in water, and a certain amount of milk put to it you know, and sweet,
 that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 What would you have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Oh jam (?) probably. Sunday we might have a bit of bacon. Probably half an egg. We would probably have a whole egg on Easter Sunday.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How about your teas when you were a boy?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Oh the same. Jam. There was no }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  cooked meals or anything like that no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Would your father have his dinner at home at mid-day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 No, my father was always away, mostly working away. He wasn't at home in the mid-day from very few jobs. The problem at our
 house was that we didn't even know he was at work for the simple reason that the public houses opened at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}}6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  o'clock{\*\xmlclose}
 in the morning although he turned out for work, many a day he came back drunk when he should be at work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 So would she, he wasn't actually working steadily then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Oh no, no. Drink, as I say, he was really classed as an alcoholic. Were it be now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Have your memories of him or were you a bit young when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Memories? Yes. I have memories of him. Not too good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Was he strict with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes, he was very short of patience which I am afraid is my failing too. My mother always used to say to him, his name was Fred, 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Frederick{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and she used to say to him "Fred it is no sooner a blow than a, a word than a blow, and the blo
w comes first" and if we did anything wrong he used to give you a bat across the ears and upstairs. As we were children. Although he had his good points. And when he was drunk he used to spend his wages, what he didn't spend on beer, he'd spend it on buyi
ng things that we didn't want and bring presents. And all that sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 What did he - did he play games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 No, I never remember him playing games with me. Although me sisters told me that my youngest sister and meself were his favou
rites. Of course I can't see it that way! I can't see it that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Had your mother ever worked before her marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes she was in service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Whereabouts was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Somewhere in Longton. I really can't tell you. There is a bit of a myste
ry about my mother. I don't really know who she was. I know what her name was, I know what her name was, and we had several relatives, but I believe that she was brought up by the family who she worked for. Yet me mother was although I suppose she was soc
ially inferior to me father, was more of a lady than me father was well a gentleman. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 In what sort of ways would this show?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Me mother? She used to help anyone in trouble. If you could speak to some of the old people down here, she used to go 
out, she would lay anyone out, do the washing for them if they were in trouble, or any confinements in the neighbourhood sort of thing, and she didn't expect anything for it. And she went to Church. Was a member of the Mothers Union.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Which one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Stoke {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}St. Peters{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. And at that time the parson used to call regularly every week and stop for a cup of tea which we never see a parson now, mind you they don't see me in church either! I am not saying anything about that now. Now my wife died in June of th
is year and she was buried up at Hartshill up there and the young parson who took the service, the service was in Stoke Parish Church, and the young parson who took the service he came to me after the service at the graveside and he asked if I would like 
him to come and see me. I said yes, come with pleasure, I would like to see him. But he hasn't been. He hasn't been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Had your parents, would they entertain or have friends or relatives in at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Oh relatives yes. Yes. From both sides, both from 
my father's side and my mother's side. And we used to go there as children, always to, I think it must have been the favourite sister, I know we used to call her Aunt Bessie and they lived near to Meir Aerodrome you know Meir, well just before you get to 
the Meir, just past the roundabout, by the Broadway cinema, there is a lot of small cottages on the left hand side, well my Auntie Bessie lived in one of them. And we used to go there, which was quite a treat for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 A regular thing was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes, perhaps every fortnight, maybe every month. Something like that. Particularly in the summer. Not the winter so much.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 After your father died had your mother any help from friends or relatives at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 No, no. She was very independent, and she was
 about 5' tall, small. And although I say it she had a heart as big as a lion. I remember going shopping with her one Friday night which was quite a treat for me because we used to have a pennorth of chips on the way back and she saw }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  men, drunk men, figh
ting and she went in between them and separated them! I don't think she was afraid of anyone. My father was a lot bigger than her and she was never afraid of him, but when he was drunk he was not fighting mad. We used to have an old sofa, maybe, could be 
here, of course it wasn't here, and she used to just, he used to come in, and she saw what state he was in and she used to just push him on the sofa and take his boots off and chuck an old coat over him and let him sleep it off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Was she house proud would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
I'd say she was to a certain point, for what furniture we'd got. She'd never learned to write until she was about fifty, and she died when she was fifty }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 7}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 . Although she could read. She had to be learnt to write her own name. But most nights she would be knitting socks or something like that, she was one of those knitters that can knit without looking at it, you know. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  steel needles, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Would she make your clothes as well or would you buy those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Well she made some. W
e had a treadle sewing machine. In the house, it stood here so she could get the light from the window, but she wore glasses. Maybe she didn't when she was young.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Had she a strict routine in her house, certain things on certain days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes. Monda
y was always washing day. I still go on that. I wash on Mondays. I do my bedrooms on a Tuesday. I go to my daughter's on a Wednesday. Thursday I clean right through from back to front.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Had your mother this sort of routine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes, Friday night was 
clearing up night at our house. And this was after, my sisters used to do that, because my mother would be doing something else. Perhaps baking. We used to have friends in of course, and she used to say, we would be sitting on a chair and my sister would 
probably be cleaning on her hands and knees with a floor cloth, and she used to say "Pick your feet up" and we had to sit like this while she did under your feet otherwise she would give your feet a smack with the wet cloth!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Had your mother special baking days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
No not particularly although usually on a Monday, I don't know why, when it was washing day, she always used to make potato cake, she used to make potato cake and cook it in the frying pan. Used Cold potatoes you know, and mash them up, and
 mix it with the flour, and perhaps a few currants in and those were usually cooked so that when we came home they were hot and she used to, when they were cooked she used to make them as big a 10" plate maybe, and she used to cut them through the middle 
and put some butter on, because there was no margarine then and butter was perhaps }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
pence a pound, or something like that, not much more. Then I don't know when she used to make the cake which we used to have at the weekend, which would be an ordinary cake 
wouldn't have any eggs in it for a start, but there would be currants in it and perhaps candied peel or raisons or something.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Had you shops nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes, yes. This street that I was born in. Do you know where the football ground is? Well coming 
to the football we'll say from Campbell Road there, straight past the Stoke end of the football ground, we lived in the first street on your right, off Lonsdale Street and on the left hand side of the street, a street called Selwyn Street so we had a shop
 on the corner. We had a shop on the corner, it isn't there now, they sold bacon slices, \{BLANK\} I think it is. But it used to be a grocers shop I remember going there when actually it was a strap \{BLANK\}
 shop, my mother paid at the weekend you see. And I w
as only a kid, I could probably only just toddle, and this shop sold all the usual things, a grocers shop, bacon and all the rest of it, and it was all strap. Well most of it I don't remember I don't think there was much ready money and she used to have a
 box of those little biscuits with little stars and different coloured sugar on them, you know, only about that far in diameter }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16395474\charrsid4203662 three }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 quarter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16395474\charrsid4203662 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  and I don't know how old I was, I shouldn't think very old, maybe }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 , and she sent me to the shop for something. An
d they were named woods, these people were, and Mrs. Wood was a bit deaf and a rather long time in coming. Anyway I helped myself to some of these biscuits out of the box, it was on the floor, on the outside of the counter you see, and I put a handful in 
m
e pocket. When I got home, I pulled them out and started to eat them. And of course my mother wanted to know where I had got them. So I told her what had happened like and she marched me straight back to this Mrs. Wood and she said "Well what are you goin
g to do with him Mrs. Wood? Are you going to fetch the policeman?" Of course she was putting the wind up me as I didn't do this sort of thing you see. And of course Mrs. Wood didn't fetch any policeman at all. That cured me anyway.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 So she would buy most things from the local shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
Yes, all except the weekend. At the weekend, this was through the week and then of course for the weekend stuff like every woman, probably every woman that we knew anyway, she went hunting round for the cheaper shops. 
And that was when we'd have these chips you see. We used to go round Stoke and find, or rather me mother did, and find the cheapest shops. You'd go to the Home and Colonial for one thing, and if butter was penny a pound cheaper somewhere else then you'd h
ave butter from there, tea from another and so on. If it was a bit cheaper. But we always finished up at this chip shop. With a pennorth of chips which we ate on the way home out of the paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Would you help your mother much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Only by errands. Onl
y by errands. I helped her afterwards at least I hope I did anyhow. After I left school. I left school when I was thirteen. My first job I had was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  bob a week which was a full time job and when I say a full time job I mean a full time job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 What were the hours?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}Half past }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 {\*\xmlclose}
 in the morning to any hour of the night that they liked to call. I worked for a woman, it was a drapers shop. It is a radio and television shop now, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Wilsons{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}, in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Liverpool Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, but at that time it was a shop by the name of But
terfield. It was lit by gas and I used to, she would insist on me lighting the gases, which was an inverted gas mantle and I must have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16395474\charrsid4203662 lit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  dozens and dozens because I had to light it with a lighter, a pole effort you know, my eyes have never been very good
 I've always worn glasses, in fact I am nearly blind in the left eye. And I used to poke this pole into these mantles and this woman used to go mad. But anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 What exactly was your job there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Errand boy, supposed to be. But I used to run erran
ds for the house, they didn't live over the shop. I used to run errands, I used to fetch fish and that. The man \{BLANK\} I think he died of cancer. He was ill from the time I was there until he died and I worked until }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  o'clock at night and then if there we
re any errands to be run she would pack me off with the errands and say "Take these will you, it is on your way home" well on me way home could mean anywhere from in this neighbourhood to as far as Trent Vale. She used to say "It is on your way home". And
 I used to go up to the top of Regent Street, I don't know if you know it, past Boother Church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 It was a fair way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 It was a fair way, yes. It meant, it could be a mile and a half to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 2}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  miles out of my road by the time I had got there and come back. I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  bob a week for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How did you get that job?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 I went for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Was it advertised or what?
