 weeks because appendicitis was a big operation then. You know. They let you convalesce there which you don't know, they are out in about a week now, aren't they, with appendicitis. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417867\charrsid4203662 
I was a bad case, the doctor let me go until they, we had a district nurse, Nurse Swan, and my mother wasn't satisfied with the doctor and he missed coming one d
ay when I was really bad and she fetched the district nurse and she came and had a look at me and she telephoned the N. Staffs Royal Infirmary and I was wrapped in a blanket, put in a cab, a horse cab at that time, and whisked straight off to the Infirmar
y and I was got ready and had the operation straight away and was operated on as soon as the doctor was ready in the operating theatre. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
And I always remember coming out of the operation and me mother was sitting by me bed, it must have been }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  or }{\rtlch\fcs1 
