t
ary bank. And the places, Doulton, Whieldon Pottery up at Mount? now, the bank where I worked, but it belonged to Winkles at that time and I used to have to carry baskets of ware on my shoulder, I was what 15, baskets of ware on me shoulders, I used to ha
ve to carry lavatory pans, you know, the ordinary lavatory pan, and the warehouse man he used to pack me off with the wares, one on me head, I used to have wear a roll in me cap, one on me head, and I used to carry one on each arm, to take them, yes.

