\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes well we were small, we were very small, so we proba
bly slept altogether in the back room, all the lot of us. I can't really remember, I can't really remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Had you any holidays as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 No. Only Sunday School treats and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Where did they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Sometimes we u
sed to go on that canal that you crossed over and we would go to Barlaston or Meaford (?), you know Meaford where the power station is, right by Stone of course, well we used to go to Meaford on a canal barge. Sometimes we would go on the train to, someti
mes we might go to Trentham Gardens, might go Trentham Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How old were you when you first went to the seaside then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 When I joined the Church Lads Brigade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417867\charrsid4203662 16 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 My first camp was at Rhyll. And then the next year 
we went to Southport. And the year of the 1914/18 War we were in camp when war was declared, the 1914/18 War at Leigh (?).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 What did you actually do at the Brigade, did you have weekly activities, what did you do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Well I was in the band, I was a
 bugler in the band. And we used to have physical drill, we used to drill with rifles, old army rifles, which probably wouldn't fire, in any case we had got no ammunition, we used to slope arms shoulder arms, present arms, and apart from that I was in the
, they had Indian clubs there, and I joined an Indian club class, we used to have social activities on Saturday night, boxing and ping pong, small billiard table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How often a week would you go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 I'd probably be going about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  nights a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Oh as much as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Oh yes. We used to have drill night, was one night. Which was all drill. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417867\charrsid4203662 
And Saturday nights was like a boys' club sort of thing. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 And then another night it would be this Indian clubs. And Friday nights was always band practice
. And the friend that I had, my mate, he was a drummer and I was a bugler. And that occupied quite a lot of time. Apart from that in the summer we used to go bathing in the canal, up at Trentham, in between Trentham and \{BLANK\}
 on that same canal that you passed over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Would you go to Sunday School as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes we went to Sunday School and I went to Bible Class. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417867\charrsid4203662 
Of course the rector of Stoke, who was the Reverend H.B.Stewart, he became Dean of Carlisle I think afterwards he was, he was Padre for the battalion which was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16395474\charrsid4203662 Hechfield}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417867\charrsid4203662  Battalion for the Church Lads Brigade. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 And my bible class parson, he was like the padre for our company, Stoke St. Peter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16395474\charrsid4203662 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 s }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
ompany you see, and he used to take bible class on Sunday afternoon, as I got older, we used to go to Bible Class on Sunday afternoon. And nearly always Church on Sunday night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How many of you would go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 To the Bible Class? Well there would be about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 30}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
. All teenagers you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Would your brothers and sisters go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes when they were younger, all of them I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How about your Mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
Oh yes, she was a member of the Mothers' Union. She went to church regularly. As I tell you the parson used to come nearly always on Friday and stop for a cup of tea, eat a bit of whatever was going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Had your mother any other outside interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 No, she'd no time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 No, I suppose not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Did I tell you she worked right up to the time that she died, more or less. In fact she worked until she was taken to her bed, sh
e died with a cancer of the liver. She only lived }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How old were you then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 21}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
 the day after my mother died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 21}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 I joined the army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Had your parents any books or newspapers in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 At that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Well as a boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Oh yes, yes. Sometimes we used to have the "Liverpool }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 W}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 eekly Post" regular. Yes, because there used to be a dialect story which we used to look forward to you know, in the Lancashire dialect
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Had they books at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Not a great m
any, we'd got Bibles, I have still got my mother's Bible and Hymn Book now but I don't think we had many books at all. There could have been a few but I wouldn't say there was many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Was your father interested in politics or Unions at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 No, I don't think he was, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How old were you when you started school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 And which school was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Stoke St. Peter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 s. The old school, it is still near the Church now, it isn't used now of course.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Was it infants mixed and then Girls and Boys separate or?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
Yes, it was infants mixed and then the boys what do you call it, the Junior was separate. Mind you, that was all in one school see. Er, and then from there, the old school is near where the Church is now, I don't think they use
d it at all now, because it is very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417867\charrsid4203662 delapidated}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
. Then I moved, when I went into the Senior class I moved into that bit of the school which is behind the football ground.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 What sort of school was that, a Board school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 No, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}St.{\*\xmlclose} Peter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 \rquote 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 s. But just, you see the Infants, the Junior down at Stoke and then that was the Senior. And I went there until I left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How old were you when you moved there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Oh somewhere about eleven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Was it any different, or was it much the same sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Well I should say it was pretty much the same. Higher degree of teaching, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How did you like school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How did I like school? I didn't dislike school at all. No. I wasn't particularly brilliant, I was very average. I liked
 painting and I liked drawing, but I never got. The top class there was what we used to called X7. And I think I finished up in 6. So you can see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Would you have stayed on if you had had any opportunity to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 No. I don't think I would. But apart 
from that I wasn't even aware that you could stop on at that time. I don't know whether you could stop on at that time. You see me at thirteen, from 1906, you are coming into 1909 aren't you, you see, so whether there was any chance of going to a Grammar 
School or anything like that, I am not even aware of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 It hadn't ever entered your head anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 No. The thing that entered my head was to go to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Was your mother interested in schooling at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 My mother? I don't know that she wa
s. No. I think that she took it as a thing that, she probably wanted us to have a schooling so that we could be better educated than what she was, I have told you she couldn't write. But apart from that it was a question of living then. Or existing, whate
ver you like to call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Who actually taught her writing then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
My sisters, my eldest sisters. She only learnt to write then because she had a bit of money in the Post Office I think and she had to sign her name, that was more or less, although sh
e could read. I don't know who taught her reading. I did have a photograph of her, but I don't know where it is, she has got a bustle, when she was 23. And she ripped it up in half and I stuck it together again and I have kept it. But it is getting very f
aded of course.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Was your mother strict over bed times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
No. I don't think she was. No because she never really had any company of me father for the simple reason, I have told you about it, about drink, that was his master, and she was only interested in the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How did you manage over baths in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Oh a tin bath. If my \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 was in here then a tin bath in the back kitchen, filled kettles and saucepans with hot water. No other meals. Or else they were all out, it was c
old you'd have it on the hearth stoke the fire, anyway, that was, then afterwards of course as we got bigger, afterwards we'd go to the public baths you see. We could go there, it was about a tanner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes, once a week. Usually Saturday morning. They provided you with one of those }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 huckaback}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  towels. Which won't dry anything at all so you took your own towel because the only thing that they gave you in the baths which had Stoke }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 aths on a red stripe and the rest was in white l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 ttering Stoke }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
aths so that it wouldn't be pinched and it was just good enough to stand on to dry your feet while you dried yourself with the ordinary Turkish towel.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Had you friends locally, were they school friends or were they neighbours children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Oh t
hey were all neighbours. Some I went to school with, some neighbours as I got in me teens and I left school. And these boys of course that I went to the Church Lads Brigade with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 There weren't any families who your mother wouldn't really want you associating with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 No I don't think she bothered, she more or less trusted us to have enough sense to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 pick}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  decent friends. If we had have picked some one that she thought were rough she wouldn't have been long in giving them? As I tell you she had a heart
 as big as a lion. She wasn't abrupt or anything like that and she wasn't aggressive in any way but she was capable of looking after herself in a quiet way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Had you ever friends in at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes, yes. We had friends in. My sisters had friends. Wel
l all of us had friends in. As I say there'd perhaps be a houseful on a Friday night, at least }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
, and there was this "Pick your feet up business" and then when they wanted to come and do that patch where you were sitting, well you had to pick your cha
ir up and take it out of the road while they did that patch and you went on patches that had been done and dried.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Would you play games or what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes, played games, draughts or snakes and ladders or something like that. I don't think we ever played cards.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417867\charrsid4203662 You said you were 15 when you started on the pot bank, how you got that job?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
Well the woman who lived across the way there she told my mother that they wanted a warehouse boy you see. And she worked there, she was one of the
se brushers that brush the sand off, as I was telling you. So it was an extra shilling a week you see. She must have spoken to the warehouseman, the chap in charge of the warehouse, and he said "Tell him to come along" and of course I went along and they 
started me. And then from there, I stopped there only about twelve months and I worked in another pot bank for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
 shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 You moved again on account of the money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 The money, yes, this increase in the money all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 What were your employers like in the first pot bank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Well I didn't see much of the employer at all. The warehouseman was my, was the chap who looked after me and he worked me to death!

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 You moved from your first pot bank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes, and I went to the second pot bank.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 What sort of job was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
This was in the warehouse, the same kind of work. And I went from very hard work to practically doing nothing at all because I just put the foreign orders out only, there was another man used to do the home o
rders, I put the foreign orders out. For the women to do. And I used to take newspapers, books, to work and I used to clear up the warehouse and I used to have a read. Everything that I could lay my hands on.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 What sort of things did you read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Newspapers, library books. I've got books here now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Which library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Stoke.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How old were you when you first started having library books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 4}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 15}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 . I read anything. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15417867\charrsid4203662 Biographies, Autobiographies, Ernest Hemingway, and I've read one or 2 Russian Dostoevesky is it? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
I can tackle most things. If they are too dry well I don't bother much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Had your warehouseman actually realized you were doing this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 No, he didn't bother. As long as I did my foreign orders, that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 What hours were you actually working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 In theory? From }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 7}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  till }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Had you any breaks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes, we used to have a half hour for breakfast and an hour for dinner, or lunch, whatever you like to call it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Would you have it there or would you go home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417867\charrsid4203662 
I'd go home for that because I was quite near to, I was on that pot bank, there isn't a pot bank there any more, you know where the Victoria Tower is on the corner here, Boother Hall Road there, that factory on your left hand side, that is now closed,
 that is where I worked, it was George Jones 'Crescent', China earthenware Potteries And there used to be rails about so high and I used to jump over the top of those, and fetch the warehouseman, who I worked under, who wasn't the head warehouseman, he us
ed to forget to bring his breakfast some mornings and I used to go onto the bank and jump over these rails and run to Trent }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 V}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417867\charrsid4203662 
ale and back again with his breakfast and get back again over the rails, through the ovens, and the sagger-house back into the warehouse.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Were they strict over time keeping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
No, they weren't strict, although you lost, if you weren't in for a certain time you lost half an hour, they let you in within a quarter of an hour, but you stood to lose half an hour. I was only getting }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  bob a week. But I don't think I ever was that, my mother would see to that in any case.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How much spending money had you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 At this place, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  bob.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 But you would hand over most of that I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Hand over that to my mother. My pocket money would only be 6d. a week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 What would you spend that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662  on}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Go the pictures probably, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 half }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 pence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
 front seats. And probably, might be chips or something else. 1d. packet of Woodbines, which you could get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
 for a penny at that time. Do a bit of smoking on the sly, not at home mind you, sent outside. Then towards the weekend if I wanted to go to the pictures again I used to say to my mother "Will you lend me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 -half }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 pence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
 or something" and she always used to lend it me but she never used to get paid back you know. She always conveniently forgot I owed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Were you involved with Unions at all at this stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 No, no. Never heard of a union at that time. No. But I stayed there until I was getting on for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662  1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  and the war had started and it fin
ished up that there was only my younger sister who was apprenticed milliner, getting no wages you see, and my mother charring, and myself. So I said "I am going to get a job in the pit and get some more money" she said "You are not going to work in the pi
t" she was always afraid of the pit and apart from that I wore glasses then, I wore glasses since I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 7}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
 you see. And but anyway I finished one afternoon, I decided to have the afternoon off and I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417867\charrsid4203662 went up}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
 to the colliery and I got a job down the pit, I came home and told my mother, she was on about breaking me neck. But anyway it turned out I went down the pit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 What sort of job was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 It was what they call taking off and waggoning the coal on the levels. Well I worked at the Glebe colliery whi
ch has closed down, it is up Fenton now and it was tremendously hot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
 well we used to walk down the dip as they call it. There was an engine that used to let }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  wagons down, and pull }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  loaded wagons up you see, and there was a level off to the right and then
 the dip continued down you see, this was going down all the time, and you used to go through a pair of doors to get the air circulation I don't know if you are familiar with pit work? Well to keep the air in, they have a door where our front door is, you
 
see, and it is a rough wooden door but it is so packed round with 'branch' as they call it which is sacking, to more or less make it air tight, and to keep the air which is already along the level where the work is see, you have got another door so the co
n
sequence is that before you, when you come through that door you have got to close that door behind you before you open this one you see, and as soon as you walked on this level as they call it, the sweat used to run out of me hair, down me face, and off 
me chin, and this was before I started to work. I used to take }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
 pints of water to work in one of those clock bottles (?) I don't know if you have seen them on the back here, I had one of those on me back and the water all used to be gone by snapping time as they called it which was round about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  o'clock, this was when we used to have, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  till }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
 this was and anyway I didn't like the pit and I thought if I get up. Because I was afraid, I used to think if I get saved today I will never come down the pit again but I was there next morning just the same.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Well me mother wanted the money. This was a rise from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  shillings a week to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 pence a day. Which was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 21/6d
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 , which was a big difference which was helping me mother. And that was the
 reason that I went down. Because actually I should never have been in the pit and when I went after this job you know, you are supposed to have an eye test, I took me glasses off of course, he didn't bother giving me an eye test at all he just gave me a 
lung check. To go and get your lamp. It's one of those rules that they conveniently forget. And I stuck it in the pit for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  or 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
 years and then me mother died in the meantime and the war was on and I had, I got used to the pit and we used to work one week days, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 , and the other night shift, from ten to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
 the next morning, well then in the summer we would perhaps go out on the Sunday evening with our best clothes on and we'd decide instead of going to work we'd have the Sunday night off you see. So we di
dn't go, so when the war was on they got us that if you lost too much time you had to face a pit committee you see because they wanted the coal for munitions you see. So as I say my time had mounted up and I had to face a pit committee so instead of facin
g a pit committee I went and joined the army.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 I see, how old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Just turned twenty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 And you stayed in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 I stayed in to the end, I stayed in until October 1919. We went out of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Belgium{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} through {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}France{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Belgium{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, into {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Germany{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, from the Armistice and I had}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662  10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  months in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Germany{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 until October 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How old were you when you were married?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 I got married in 1924. If my wife had lived until this month, until the 27}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\super\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  of this month, we should have been married 44 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How did you first meet her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
Well she lived near to for one thing and neighbours round this area you see, a gang of lads talking to a gang of girls and that sort of thing. But this was at the time I was in the Church Lads Brigade and I wrote to he
r while I was in the army and when I came back I met her again and we went out together and we got married in 1924. Married in 1924. 44 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 How did your mother think of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 My mother was dead of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 When you first started going around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
My mother didn't know. She didn't know. I think she would probably be like all mothers. No girl would be good enough for her son which is the usual thing I think isn't it? I don't think it applies the other way. With daughters.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 You said you moved house in, first you moved to Mount .. (interviewee) .. Pleasant, yes. Where actually was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Well, it was a big, er, house. It was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  bedrooms and we were a big family. I don't know whether I told you, there was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 7}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 , }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 7}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  of us. And then you moved again about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  years later and moved down to this area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes, down, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Why did you move that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Well, my father died while we lived at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Mount Pleasant
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and my eldest brother got married, and, er, 'twas cheaper, the house was cheaper, there was less rent, and that was the reason.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 You said your father was a stonemason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Ye-.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Had he always been a stonemason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 He started straight after leaving school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 As far as I know, yes. You must bear in mind that I was only }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11037295\charrsid4203662 10 }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 when he died.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Did he have any casual or part time jobs apart from his main job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 He did work on his own some nights. He did gravestones for people, you know, carved gravestones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 So he made a bit of extra money this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 You said your mother was - she didn't do any work until after your father died, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Did she work then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes, she did charring and taking washing in and all that, that sort of thing because my father, I think I told you, was a drunkard.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 So was she out of the house when you were still small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
No, I, I, I can't remember her being out of the house for the simple reason that when she did washing, you see, the washing came to our house and was done from, from the house and she ironed it, and it was taken to the people who she was doing it for.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 She wasn't ever out charring at all when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 No, no. That came after.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 You said your mother made most of your family's clothes, would she buy as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
Oh, yes, yes, yes, she bought, er, well, I, I don't remember about my clothes, all as I remember is her buying me suits when I got old, you know, but we had a machine and, and it, and it always stood in, like if it had been this house stood in the co
rner, and it was drawn in front of the window and she got the light so she could do the sewing there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 She always bought your shoes, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Would you have them mended at a cobblers or would somebody mend them at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 No, my father mended them, while he was alive, and of course after they went to the cobblers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Did your father do any other things which helped your mother about the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 No, I, I, I don't think the fact that he, he did gravestones helped my mother at all for the simple reason that he, he spent it on drink.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 You said you helped your mother by running errands for her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 (interviewee) Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Did your other brothers and sisters help in any way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Oh yes, er, there was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 7}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  of us and I was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 th, I was above the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 7}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 th. I had one sister younger than myself, and by the time some of my, er, brothers or sisters were out at work, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Did your older sisters actually help your mother when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 I, I suppose they looked after me, I, I, I can't really remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Was your mother strict over bedtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 I don't think so, not particularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 Would she, or one of your sisters, put you to bed when you were still small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 No, I can't remember, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14504576 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 When you were at school, would you all have breakfast as a family in the morning, or would you all be going out at different times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751724 JH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662 
Well, we probably, people going out at different times. Some of them would be up before me, going to work, as working times then were, wer
e much earlier than what they are now. Now when I went to work, er, I've tried, my first job, of course, was, er, running errands at (?) shop and then I went on pot bank, pot factory, and, er, I think I told you, we wouldn't close there, we started work a
t }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 7}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  o'clock in the morning till }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  o'clock at night. You see, well, they probably started at the same time, well I wouldn't be going to school, I think school started at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14698603\charrsid4203662 9}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15412957\charrsid4203662  o'clock, so probably myself and younger sister when she went to school, we'd have breakfast later.
\par 
