If it was getting towards Christmas we'd, we'd be busy helping mother make the Christmas pudding and mince pies, used to have those big raisins and they had seeds in, and you used to have to break them open and pull th
e pips out, and sometimes we'd stop, we used to have a bowl of water, you'd keep on dipping your fingers in to wash the pip off and to, gets the stickiness off your finger for the next one. I don't remember seedless raisins.
